        },
        "subject": "LU-12367 llite: Disable strided readahead",
        "message": "LU-12367 llite: Disable strided readahead\n\nThe current strided readahead is partly broken for normal\nuse, and does not correctly recognize unaligned reads, so\nit is actively harmful for the IOR hard read test.\n\nThis patch is a quick hack to disable it, which should\nresult in significantly fewer small read RPCs during that\ntest.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I11fe566b2116b8e4f30d0768b1d9aedee89da95e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
